==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[never look a gift horse in the mouth]]

===Etymology===
Horses' gums recede as they age making the teeth appear to grow long. Therefore, inspecting the teeth of a horse given as a gift would mean that recipient is trying to see if the horse is old (undesirable) or young (more desirable).

